{"id":2866,"date":"2022-11-22T13:32:31","date_gmt":"2022-11-22T12:32:31","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/?page_id=2866"},"modified":"2023-01-27T12:14:41","modified_gmt":"2023-01-27T11:14:41","slug":"travel-information","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/events\/travel-information\/","title":{"rendered":"Travel Information"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"modal-ready\">\n<div class=\"is-layout-flex wp-container-3 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p><a href=\"#venue\" data-type=\"internal\" data-id=\"#venue\"><strong>Venue<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"#how-to-get-to-bonn\" data-type=\"internal\" data-id=\"#how-to-get-to-bonn\"><strong>How to get to Bonn<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"#how-to-get-to-the-venue\" data-type=\"internal\" data-id=\"#how-to-get-to-the-venue\"><strong>How to get to the venue<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"#hotels-and-accomodations\" data-type=\"internal\" data-id=\"#hotels-and-accomodations\"><strong>Hotels and accommodation shortlist<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Dear Guests,&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">We are pleased to welcome you to the final Gotriple Conference in Bonn. We want to share some travel information to make your stay more comfortable and enjoyable. In this Brochure, you will find important information regarding travelling to Bonn and where to stay.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">First of all, we highly advise you to keep in mind that many restaurants and cafes in Germany accept cash only. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Covid Restrictions<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As of the 1st of February, Covid Restrictions in Germany will be lifted. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<div class=\"is-layout-flex wp-container-6 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"Venue\"><strong>Venue<\/strong><\/h2>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Bonn Science Center (Wissenschaftszentrum)&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bonn Ahrstr. 45 53175 Bonn \u260f +49 0228 302219<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a central conference venue in the Bonn region and a location for many renowned science organizations, the Science Center stands for a unique communication concept: It offers science a platform for networking and dialogue with business, politics and the public.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Bonn Science Center is conveniently located and easy to reach by car and public transport. It is connected via several highways, the railroad stations Bonn and Bonn-Bad Godesberg, and the airport Cologne\/Bonn.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"How-to-get-to-bonn\"><strong>How to get to Bonn<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>From D\u00fcsseldorf Airport (DUS)<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest and fastest way to travel to Bonn from D\u00fcsseldorf Airport is to use the regional express train RB5, which departs every hour and connects the airport to Bonn central station in about an hour. A one-way ticket costs 19,60\u20ac and needs to be purchased online. You can purchase a discounted city ticket for public transportation in Bonn along with your DB train ticket; it will be valid until 03.00 PM the next day. Buy tickets here: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bahn.com\/en\">Cheap Train Tickets | Timetables for Germany &amp; Europe &#8211; Deutsche Bahn<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/lh3.googleusercontent.com\/YUOQNOgOLHl44sotIrFYpBM7e7-mkL_7VgHBNpQ_Fp9Lfp2sD2bUrjxhCbJfXAX2vaU1L5szF3WbpBz89F5Kuwq_DPXzJ1ZD32xsRbU-uVnbNj1CRbX33rZNpzURr4NCbguzombtzNVMviC8RBt2u9qOkNCjssApiXKfGcZZ4qP-k9ws0TRH2gs7CHWFwIgL\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>From Frankfurt International Airport (FRA)<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to travel to Bonn from Frankfurt International Airport is to use the InterCity Express train (ICE). First, you will need to get to Siegburg train station using ICE trains, then take the Tram 66<strong> Bad Honnef<\/strong> and get off at Bonn central station. Additionally, you can purchase a discounted city ticket for public transportation in Bonn along with your DB train ticket; it will be valid until 03.00 PM the next day. You can purchase train tickets here: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bahn.com\/en\">Cheap Train Tickets | Timetables for Germany &amp; Europe &#8211; Deutsche Bahn<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>From K\u00f6ln\/Bonn Airport (CGN)<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We highly recommend getting a 24h BONN REGIO WELCOME CARD; with this ticket, you can use every means (excluding ICE) of transport in Bonn or\/and Cologne for 24 hours and get discounts on various tourist attractions such as museums. You will need to renew the ticket every 24h. The tickets can be purchased using SWB: EASY GO app (available in English).&nbsp; For more information please check the flyer here: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonn-region.de\/services\/files\/broschueren\/Flyer_BRWC_Englisch_2020.pdf\">Flyer_BTHVN_2020_englisch_print.indd (bonn-region.de)<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Bus<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>SB60 Bonn Hbf 30 min. K\u00f6ln\/Bonn Airport Terminal 1\/2 (bus stop 5) (BONN REGIO WELCOME CARD INCLUDES TICKETS FOR SB60)&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Airport Express Bus SB60 provides the most uncomplicated transportation for most travellers between downtown Bonn and Cologne-Bonn Airport (CGN). SB60 runs every 30 minutes.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Train<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>S19<strong> Au(Sieg) Bf<\/strong> &gt; Change in <strong>Siegburg Bf<\/strong> &gt; Tram 66<strong> Bad Honnef<\/strong> \u2013 Bonn<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Taxi<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Bonn Zentrum 22 km 15 min. 40\u20ac&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"how-to-get-to-the-venue\"><strong>How to get to the venue<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>From K\u00f6ln\/Bonn Airport&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Bus<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>SB60 Bonn Hbf 30 min. K\u00f6ln\/Bonn Airport Terminal 1\/2 (Bus stop 5) -&gt; change in <strong>Bonn Hbf <\/strong>&gt; Tram 16,63 to <strong>Bad Godesberg Stadthalle<\/strong> &gt; <strong>Hochkreuz<\/strong>, then 8 min walking.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Train<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>S19<strong> Au(Sieg) Bf<\/strong> &gt; change in <strong>Siegburg Bf<\/strong> &gt; Tram 66 to<strong> Bad Honnef<\/strong> &gt; change in <strong>Bonn Hbf <\/strong>&gt;&nbsp; Tram 16, 63 to Hochkreuz &#8211; 8 min walking<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>From Bonn Zentrum&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Bonn Hbf<\/strong> Tram 16\/66 to <strong>Bad Godesberg Stadthalle<\/strong> &gt; <strong>Hochkreuz, <\/strong>then 8 min walking.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"hotels-and-accomodations\"><strong>Hotels and accommodation shortlist<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Bad Godesberg (close to the conference venue)<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Best Western Hotel Kaiserhof<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>~112\u20ac Bad Godesberg, Moltkestra\u00dfe 64, 53173 Bonn (2.8km to the venue)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Mail: <a href=\"mailto:booking.service@bestwestern.com\">booking.service@bestwestern.com<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u260f: +49 800 2125888<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Website: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bestwestern.de\/?etcc_med=SEA&amp;etcc_cmp=ecommerce&amp;etcc_par=SEA_Brand&amp;etcc_var=Brand_DE&amp;etcc_plc=Search&amp;etcc_tar=Brand&amp;iata=00167770&amp;gclid=343acc0cf8af1a5795f5af